1 Download ISO http://old-releases.ubuntu.com/releases/6.06.0/ Then Select Desktop CD Then Download Which architecture (NOT 64-bit PC AMD64)
2 Flash The ISO From USB Stick
3 Then When on installer menu enter Start or install ubuntu
4 After installation finished reboot and Login To Desktop
5 Run sudo nano /etc/lsb-release
  Then change DISTRIB_ID=Ubuntu To DISTRIB_ID=Syslack Linux
  Then change DISTRIB_RELEASE=6.06 To DISTRIB_RELEASE=1.1
  Then change DISTRIB_CODENAME=dapper to DISTRIB_CODENAME=viprin
  Then Change DISTRIB_DESCRIPTION="Ubuntu 6.06.1 LTS" To DISTRIB_DESCRIPTION="Syslack Linux"
6 Go To Theme Preferences Then Select Clearlooks Instead Of Human
7 Open sessions then Disable Show splash screen on login then Enable Automatically save changes to session
8 Run sudo nano /boot/grub/menu.lst then change timeout 3 to 5 then add # on hiddenmenu example # hiddenmenu
  on End Default Options Change title Ubuntu To Syslack Linux On Every Beginning Even recovery mode and memtest86+ then remove quiet splash
  never update grub because you don’t actually need to run sudo update-grub since Syslack Linux For Legacy x86 32 bit,Mac (PowerPC) and IBM-PPC (POWER5),SPARC,HP PA-RISC,IA-64 uses grub legacy Which GRUB legacy reads menu.lst directly at boot, so changes take effect immediately.
9 Run sudo nano /etc/issue then change Ubuntu 6.06.1 LTS \n \l To Syslack Linux \n \l
  Then change sudo nano /etc/issue.net then change Ubuntu 6.06.1 LTS To Syslack Linux
10 Run sudo nano /etc/gdm/gdm.conf then add # On GraphicalTheme=Human And remove # On GraphicalThemes=circles/:happygnome Example #GraphicalTheme=Human And GraphicalThemes=circles/:happygnome
   Ctrl x y enter
11 Run sudo rm /etc/motd
12 Go to Sound Preferences then
   For Choose menu item select Beep
   For Click on command button select click
   For Error message Select Siren
   For informational message select Boing
13 Edit apt sources using sudo nano /etc/apt/sources.list
   Then remove Line commented out by installer and Replace existing lines with old-releases URLs
   Use this template

deb http://old-releases.ubuntu.com/ubuntu dapper main restricted universe multiverse
deb-src http://old-releases.ubuntu.com/ubuntu dapper main restricted universe multiverse

deb http://old-releases.ubuntu.com/ubuntu dapper-updates main restricted universe multiverse
deb-src http://old-releases.ubuntu.com/ubuntu dapper-updates main restricted universe multiverse

deb http://old-releases.ubuntu.com/ubuntu dapper-security main restricted universe multiverse
deb-src http://old-releases.ubuntu.com/ubuntu dapper-security main restricted universe multiverse

deb http://old-releases.ubuntu.com/ubuntu dapper-backports main restricted universe multiverse
deb-src http://old-releases.ubuntu.com/ubuntu dapper-backports main restricted universe multiverse

Update package lists
sudo apt-get update

14 Run sudo apt-get install gnome-backgrounds
   Then select wallpaper you want example GNOME Curves

15 Run sudo apt-get install gnome-audio
   Then add toggled.wav for Select check box
   Then add generic.wav for Miscellaneous message
   Then add question wav for question dialog
   Then add warning.wav for Warning message
   Then reboot

16 If you see Replace configuration file /etc/issue.net Click keep immediately

17 If you got on minimal you can run sudo nano ~/.bash_profile then add this

if [[ -z $DISPLAY ]] && [[ $(tty) = /dev/tty1 ]]; then
    exec startx
fi

Or You can reinstall gdm by running sudo apt-get install gdm

